"'''Love the Way You Lie'''" is a song by the American [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] recording artist [[Eminem]] from his seventh studio album ''[[Recovery (Eminem album)|Recovery]]'' (2010). [[Skylar Grey]], a singer-songwriter, wrote and recorded the [[demo (music)|demo]] alongside the producer [[Alex da Kid]] when she felt she was in an abusive romantic relationship with the music industry. Eminem wrote the verses and chose the Barbadian singer [[Rihanna]] to sing the chorus; their past experiences in difficult relationships influenced the collaboration. Recording sessions were held in [[Ferndale, Michigan]], and [[Dublin, Ireland]]. Backed by guitar, piano and violin, the track is a [[Tempo (music)|midtempo]] hip hop [[ballad]] with a [[Pop music|pop]] refrain and describes two lovers who refuse to separate despite being in a dangerous [[love<U+2013>hate relationship]].

[[Interscope Records]] released the song in August 2010 as the second single from ''Recovery''. Critics praised its melody but were divided on thematic aspects such as poignancy and accuracy. Eminem promoted the single with performances at the [[Electronic Entertainment Expo 2010|2010 Electronic Entertainment Expo]], the [[2010 MTV Video Music Awards]] and [[music festival|festivals]]. The music video, directed by [[Joseph Kahn]], stars [[Dominic Monaghan]] and [[Megan Fox]] in a violent relationship and shows Eminem and Rihanna in front of a burning house. The clip had a mixed reception due to scenes of [[domestic violence]]. Reporters suggested that the song and its accompanying video were influenced by Eminem's and Rihanna's relationships with their respective ex-lovers Kimberly Scott and [[Chris Brown (American entertainer)|Chris Brown]]. 

Critics listed "Love the Way You Lie" among the best tracks of 2010 and of Eminem's career. The song won many awards and received five [[Grammy Award|Grammy]] nominations. It is Eminem's best-selling single and was number one on twenty-six [[record chart]]s, including the United States' [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] for seven&nbsp;weeks. The single sold more than five&nbsp;million copies in the US and was the [[List of best-selling singles by year (UK)|best-selling song of 2010 in the United Kingdom]]. Musical acts such as [[Cher Lloyd]] and [[The Band Perry]] performed [[cover versions]]. Rihanna has said that the theme of domestic violence, a topic on which she claims many people do not have insight, is what makes the song effective. She later recorded "[[Love the Way You Lie (Part II)]]", narrated mostly from her perspective.

==Writing and production==
[[File:RihannaLastGirlOnEarthFMar2011.jpg|thumb|upright|Rihanna's approval of the song's topic ultimately influenced her decision to work with Eminem.|alt=Rihanna with red, long hair and a dress with floral patterns. Her left hand is raised and her right hand holds a microphone near her mouth.]]

Development of "Love the Way You Lie" began with the backing track and [[Hook (music)|hook]] melody, which were created by the British [[hip hop music|hip hop]] producer [[Alex da Kid]].<ref name=sos/> He spent hours making [[loop (music)|loop]]s and produced an electronic drum rhythm before adding live instrumentation. The drums were [[Sampling (music)|sampled]] from live recordings he had saved.<ref name=sosii/> Alex da Kid recorded an [[acoustic guitar]] for the verses with a [[Georg Neumann]] U87 microphone and an Avid Mbox audio interface. He told ''[[Sound on Sound]]'' magazine that this song had given him an opportunity to reintroduce live guitar in hip hop music.<ref name="sosii">{{Cite journal|first=Paul|last=Tingen|title=Alex Da Kid: Songwriter & Producer|journal=Sound on Sound|publisher=SOS Publications Group|month=December|year=2011|issn=0951-6816|pages=64<U+2013>7|issue=2|volume=27}}</ref> During the session, he used [[Waves Audio|Waves]] RVerb and REQ equalization on his main [[Bass drum|kick]] track and a MaxxBass plug-in on two others.<ref name=sos/>

Writing began in late 2009, when the American singer [[Skylar Grey|Holly Brook Hafermann]] resided at the Artula Retreat in [[Bandon, Oregon]],<ref name="theworldlink">{{cite news|last=Dombrowski|first=Chris|title=Going to Grammys|url=http://theworldlink.com/news/local/article_4f9bdb96-30fe-11e0-9f4b-001cc4c002e0.html|accessdate=November 13, 2011|work=[[The World (Coos Bay)|The World]]|publisher=[[Lee Enterprises]]|date=February 5, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/69v0pEve8|archivedate=August 14, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> and composed songs.<ref name=spin/> Later in New York, under her new stage name Skylar Grey, she visited her [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]] publisher [[Jennifer Blakeman]] to seek help presenting her work;<ref name=spin/><ref name=parlay>{{cite journal|title=The Right Hookup|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=March 12, 2011|first=Gail|last=Mitchell|volume=123|issue=8|issn=0006-2510|page=20}}</ref> Blakeman suggested she collaborate with Alex da Kid.<ref name=spin>{{cite web|url=http://www.spin.com/articles/skylar-grey-changeling|first=David|last=Marchese|title=Skylar Grey: The Changeling|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|publisher=Spin Media LLC|date=June 10, 2011|accessdate=February 19, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/69v0wEjeL|archivedate=August 14, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> The producer emailed Grey his track, which suggested a theme of abusive romantic relationships to her as she spontaneously sang lyrics to the melody.<ref name=ewltwyl>{{cite web|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2011/02/22/skylar-grey-interview-eminem-dr-dre/|first=Mandi|last=Bierly|title=Skylar Grey talks penning 'I Need a Doctor,' her name change, and why her upcoming album may have a sound we've never heard before|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time Inc]]|date=February 22, 2011|accessdate=October 10, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/634kVJBLv|archivedate=November 9, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> She told the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' that she was in an abusive relationship with the [[music industry]]: "I love it so much, and I give it all that I have, yet it beats me down."<ref name="latimesmag" /> This idea inspired her writing,<ref name="latimesmag" /> a process she found came naturally, as if she were creating an [[alternative pop]] song for herself.<ref name=parthiphop/> She wrote the [[Refrain|chorus]] to "Love the Way You Lie" in fifteen&nbsp;minutes and recorded vocals for Alex da Kid's [[Demo (music)|demo]].<ref name=spin/><ref name=rsem/>

In early 2010, Alex da Kid offered the [[Shady Records]] Senior Director [[Rigo "Riggs" Morales]] some backing tracks.<ref name="rapup" /> Morales enjoyed the tracks and sent them to [[Eminem]], who was seeking a different musical approach for his next album.<ref name="rapup">{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2010/06/14/qa-producer-alex-da-kid-talks-eminem/|first=Georgette|last=Cline|title=Q&A: Producer Alex da Kid talks Eminem|work=[[Rap-Up]]|publisher=Devin Lazerine|accessdate=July 27, 2011|date=June 14, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62GWVxbqU|archivedate=October 7, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Impressed with Alex da Kid's work, Eminem asked for more tracks and subsequently heard "Love the Way You Lie". He chose it and told his manager [[Paul Rosenberg (music manager)|Paul Rosenberg]] he wanted to collaborate with the Barbadian singer [[Rihanna]].<ref name="rapup" /> Eminem told Skyrock FM, "It's one of those tracks that I felt like only she could pull it off."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2010/06/01/eminem-talks-rihanna-pink-and-lil-wayne-collaborations/|title=Eminem talks Rihanna, Pink, and Lil Wayne collaborations|work=Rap-Up|publisher=Devin Lazerine|accessdate=August 11, 2011|archivedate=October 6, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62F6m77xk|deadurl=no}}</ref> Rosenberg sent the track to Rihanna, who accepted Eminem's request "at the last moment."<ref name="rapup" /> Eminem then wrote the rapped verses.<ref name="rsem">{{cite web|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/photos/how-10-major-songwriters-make-big-money-20120119/eminem-co-writer-love-the-way-you-lie-0981130|title=How 10 Major Songwriters Make Big Money: Eminem, Co-Writer, 'Love the Way You Lie'|accessdate=January 21, 2012|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=Wenner Media|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6JFGbfHOB|archivedate=August 29, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> 

Rihanna said she joined the collaboration because she could relate to the theme of the song, as she and Eminem had been in difficult relationships on "different ends of the table".<ref name="sodeep">{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/rihanna-talks-eminem-duet-and-katy-perrys-bachelorette-party-singer-to-star-in-first-movie_article_35010|title=Rihanna Talks Eminem Duet & Katy Perry's Bachelorette Party; Singer To Star In First Movie|work=[[Access Hollywood]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=July 26, 2010|accessdate=October 5, 2011|archivedate=October 6, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62F6XRDyk|deadurl=no}}</ref> Eminem had released the songs "[['97 Bonnie & Clyde]]" (1998) and "[[Kim (song)|Kim]]" (2000), in which he fantasizes respectively about murdering and verbally abusing his then-wife Kimberly Scott.<ref>{{cite web|author=Toure|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/the-marshall-mathers-lp-20000706|title=''The Marshall Mathers LP''|work=Rolling Stone|publisher=Wenner Media|date=July 6, 2000|accessdate=September 6, 2013}}</ref> They had divorced in 2001 and again in 2006 after a remarriage.<ref name=divorce>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/6195977.stm|title=Eminem divorces for second time|work={{noitalic|[[BBC News]]}}|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=December 20, 2006|accessdate=August 26, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AD5UiXU4|archivedate=August 26, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> In February 2009, Rihanna's relationship with [[Chris Brown (American entertainer)|Chris Brown]], an American singer, had ended following his felony assault on her.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spin.com/articles/chris-brown-and-rihanna-whole-story|first=Melissa|last=Goldstein|title=Chris Brown and Rihanna: The Whole Story|work=Spin|publisher=Spin Media LLC|date=February 12, 2009|accessdate=February 25, 2012}}</ref> Rihanna described "Love the Way You Lie" as unique, realistic and deep, saying it "broke down the cycle of domestic violence" because few people had insight on the topic.<ref name="sodeep" /><ref name="James Dinh">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1641998/rihanna-tells-story-behind-eminem-duet-love-way-lie.jhtml|first=James|last=Dinh|title=Rihanna Tells Story Behind Eminem Duet, 'Love The Way You Lie'|work={{noitalic|[[MTV News]]}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=June 21, 2010|accessdate=August 11, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62F6fHz6o|archivedate=October 6, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="howdid" />

==Recording==
Mike Strange recorded and [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixed]] Eminem's vocals at Effigy Studios in [[Ferndale, Michigan]].<ref name="notes" /> The sessions took two days.<ref>{{Cite journal|first=Monica|last=Herrera|title=Alex Da Kid: The British Songwriter/Producer Behind Two Of The Smashes Of The Season Details His Path To Success|date=August 21, 2010|journal=Billboard|volume=122|page=18|issue=33|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|issn=0006-2510|editor-first=Danyel|editor-last=Smith}}</ref> Strange edited the vocals with D-Verb<U+2014>a [[reverberation]] software<U+2014>and an Extra Long Delay plug-in.<ref name="sos" /> He preferred to make few changes; for "Love the Way You Lie" he almost exclusively used board [[Dynamic range compression|compression]] and console [[equalization (audio)|equalization]]. Strange used the Bricasti and Eventide Reverb 2016 mixing tools for "brighter" reverberation.<ref name="sos" /> Detroit musician [[Luis Resto (musician)|Luis Resto]] has contributed to the arrangement on many of Eminem's songs, but did not do so for "Love the Way You Lie".<ref name=sos/> According to Strange, "Everything we needed was already in the track, apart from the vocals."<ref name="sos">{{cite web|url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/oct10/articles/it-1010.htm|first=Paul|last=Tingen|title=Secrets Of The Mix Engineers: Mike Strange Jr|work=[[Sound on Sound]]|publisher=SOS Publications Group|accessdate=August 26, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62GWeVVzH|archivedate=October 7, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Two to three&nbsp;weeks after the sessions, Alex da Kid arrived to help mix and [[Audio mastering|master]] the track.<ref name=rapup/> He wanted to replace the acoustic guitar on the demo, but Eminem chose to keep it.<ref name=sosii/> Strange said, "It was simply a matter of trying to match and then to improve on the demo [Alex da Kid]'d sent us."<ref name="sos" /> Strange's brother Joe [[audio engineering|engineered]] the track.<ref name=notes/>

Rihanna's recording sessions took place at Sun Studios in Dublin, Ireland. Marcos Tovar mixed her vocals, which were engineered by Spike Lindsey and mastered from Detroit over the Internet.<ref name=rapup/><ref name=notes/> The American songwriter [[Makeba Riddick]] provided additional vocal production.<ref name="notes" /> Strange used equalization, compression and reverberation but left the vocal balance.<ref name=sos/> He assumed that Rihanna was satisfied with her recorded vocals and did not make major changes on her seven stereo vocal tracks.<ref name=sos/>

==Composition==
{{Listen
| filename    = Love the Way You Lie.ogg
| title       = "Love the Way You Lie"
| description = A 26-second song sample. Backed by an electric guitar and a piano,<ref name=sosii/><ref name=dscom/> Rihanna sings the second half of the chorus in a sad voice without [[vibrato]].<ref name="nytltwyl"/> Eminem begins the second verse over an acoustic guitar, violin and drums, expressing frustration in his voice.<ref name=sosii/><ref name=pound/><ref name="timetop10"/>
}}
"Love the Way You Lie" is a [[Tempo|midtempo]] hip hop [[ballad]].<ref name="parthiphop">{{cite web|url=http://rapfix.mtv.com/2011/04/14/skylar-grey-talks-becoming-a-part-of-hip-hop/|first=Kathy|last=Iandoli|title=Skylar Grey Talks Becoming A Part Of Hip Hop|work={{noitalic|[[MTV]]}}|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]|date=April 14, 2011|accessdate=August 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62F7dPBw9|archivedate=October 6, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name=bill/><ref name=mtvsingle>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1642772/20100630/eminem.jhtml|title=How Did Eminem's ''Recovery'' Have Such A Big Debut?|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|date=June 30, 2010|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|accessdate=July 1, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62GWaZfxP|archivedate=October 7, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> The lyrics describe a couple's refusal to separate despite having an abusive relationship.<ref name=bbc/> According to the sheet music from [[Universal Music Publishing Group]], the song is in the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[G minor]] with a [[common time|common time signature]] and a tempo of 84&nbsp;[[beats per minute]].<ref name=sheet/> The [[vocal range]] spans from [[B<U+266D> (musical note)|B{{music|flat}}<sub>3</sub>]] to [[D (musical note)|D<sub>5</sub>]].<ref name="sheet">{{cite web |title=Digital Sheet Music&nbsp;<U+2013> Eminem&nbsp;<U+2013> Love the Way You Lie |year=2010 |work={{noitalic|Musicnotes.com}}|publisher=[[Universal Music Publishing Group]]|last=Mathers|first=Marshall|last2=Hafferman|first2=Holly|authorlink2=Skylar Grey|last3=Grant|first3=Alexander|authorlink3=Alex da Kid|id=MN0085288|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0085288}}</ref> "Love the Way You Lie" opens as Rihanna sings the [[pop music|pop]] refrain over a piano:<ref name=dscom>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.ca/music/albumreviews/a234775/eminem-recovery.html|first=Mayer|last=Nissem|title=Eminem: 'Recovery'&nbsp;<U+2013> Review|work={{noitalic|[[Digital Spy]]}}|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi M<U+00E9>dias]]|date=June 21, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636R1a1mH|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name=timetop10/>

<blockquote>
Just gonna stand there and watch me burn<br>
But that's alright, because I like the way it hurts.<br>
Just gonna stand there and hear me cry<br>
But that's alright, because I love the way you lie.<ref name=bbc/></blockquote>

The refrain is based on a Gm<U+2013>E{{music|flat}}<sub>(add2)</sub><U+2013>B{{music|flat}}<U+2013>F/A [[chord progression]].<ref name=sheet/> Fraser McAlphine of the [[BBC]] wrote that Rihanna feels confined "in a cell of [her] own creation".<ref name=bbc/> She sings without [[vibrato]],<ref name="nytltwyl">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/26/arts/music/26browne.html|first=David|last=Brownie|title=Trilling Songbirds Clip Their Wings|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|date=December 24, 2011|accessdate=December 19, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ABcqdJYG|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> a pulsating musical effect used to add expression.<ref>{{cite book|first=Karen|last=Sell|title=The Disciplines Of Vocal Pedagogy: Towards An Holistic Approach|publisher=[[Ashgate Publishing]]|year=2005|isbn=075465169X|page=118}}</ref> One commentator, ''[[The New York Times]]''{{'}} David Brownie, wrote that despite this, her voice subtly shows grief and regret.<ref name="nytltwyl"/> Eminem then "zap[s] out into a ballady rap":<ref name=dscom/> "I can't tell you what it really is/ I can only tell you what it feels like."<ref name=timetop10/> The verses follow a Gm<U+2013>E{{music|flat}}<sub>(add2)</sub>B{{music|flat}}<U+2013>Fsus/A chord progression.<ref name=sheet/> Eminem regrets an end to an abusive, failed relationship, describing mutual violence and expressing both fondness and anger.<ref name=leak/><ref name="asspress">{{Cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com/view/full_story/9032280/article-Is-violent-Rihanna-Eminem-song-a-teaching-tool-|first=Jocelyn|last=Noveck|title=Is violent Rihanna<U+2013>Eminem song a teaching tool?|work=[[Herald Sun]]|publisher=[[The Herald and Weekly Times]]|accessdate=December 18, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/640uKkQau|archivedate=December 17, 2011}}</ref> The two artists' characters are portrayed in a romantic relationship when he responds to Rihanna by concluding the verse: "I laid hands on her. I'll never stoop so low again/ I guess I don't know my own strength."<ref name=bbc/> Rihanna sings the chorus again, backed by an [[electric guitar]] and a piano.<ref name=sosii/><ref name=dscom/>

Acoustic guitar, violin and drums accompany Eminem's verses.<ref name=sosii/><ref name=pound>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2010-08-06/entertainment/27071941_1_rihanna-domestic-violence-megan-fox|title=Dominic Monaghan and Megan Fox play with fire in Eminem's 'Love the Way You Lie' video|first=Anthony|last=Benigno|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|publisher=[[Mortimer Zuckerman]]|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=January 26, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DFXO32ME|archivedate=December 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> The lyrics transition from discussing positive aspects of love to describing violent events.<ref name=asspress/> Eminem raps, "It's the rage that took over, it controls you both, so they say it's best to go your separate ways. Guess that they don't know ya, cause today that was yesterday."<ref name=atlantic/> Sady Doyle of ''[[The Atlantic]]'' interpreted these lyrics as the rapper's confession to having abused Scott, as he "turns the anger and accusations toward himself".<ref name=atlantic/> In the second verse, Eminem accepts the outcome after feeling sorry, as he admits, "Yesterday is over, it's a different day."<ref name="leak" /> His frustration increases and he raps that two personalities can clash and devastate: "maybe that's what happens when a tornado meets a volcano".<ref name="timetop10">{{cite web|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2035319_2034688_2034658,00.html|first=Claire|last=Suddath|title=5. Eminem featuring Rihanna, 'Love the Way You Lie'|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|publisher=Time Inc|date=December 9, 2010|accessdate=November 5, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/634koGo0g|archivedate=November 9, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name=bbc/> The described [[love<U+2013>hate relationship]] worsens and leads to [[domestic violence]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://arts.nationalpost.com/2011/02/10/can-eminem-win-a-grammy-hoodie-trick/|first=Lynn|last=Saxberg|title=Can Eminem win a Grammy hoodie trick?|work=[[National Post]]|publisher=[[Postmedia Network]]|date=February 11, 2011|accessdate=February 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DqtMyotZ|archivedate=January 22, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> Eminem admits to lying about promises he makes and says late in the song,<ref name=asspress/> "If she ever tries to fuckin' leave again, I'ma tie her to the bed and set this house on fire",<ref name=lyricnotes>{{Cite album-notes|year=2010|title=Recovery|artist=Eminem|publisher=Interscope Records|publisherid=2739452|page=14|location=Santa Monica}}</ref> a reference to Rihanna's lyrics.<ref name=asspress/>

==Release and response==
On May 27, 2010, Eminem revealed the title of "Love the Way You Lie" as part of the tracklist of his seventh studio album ''[[Recovery (Eminem album)|Recovery]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1640237/eminems-recovery-track-list-revealed-lil-wayne-rihanna-guest.jhtml|first=Jayson|last=Rodriguez|title=Eminem's ''Recovery'' Track List Revealed: Lil Wayne, Rihanna Guest|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=May 27, 2010|accessdate=August 25, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62F6P3Nny|archivedate=October 6, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> which came out on June 21, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/recovery-r1813674|first=David|last=Jeffries|title=''Recovery''&nbsp;<U+2013> Eminem|work={{noitalic|[[AllMusic]]}}|publisher=[[All Media Guide]]|date=June 21, 2010|accessdate=February 25, 2012}}</ref> Initially a radio single,<ref name=holdoff/> the song was released later by [[Polydor Records]] as a [[compact disc single|CD]] in the United Kingdom on August 9, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.co.uk/Love-Way-You-Eminem-Rihanna/dp/B003VY4LIO|title=Eminem feat. Rihanna&nbsp;<U+2013> 'Love the Way You Lie' (UK single)|publisher=[[Amazon.com]] (UK)|date=August 9, 2010|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref> [[Interscope Records]] distributed it in Germany on August 20.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.de/dp/B003VY4LIO |title=Eminem feat. Rihanna&nbsp;<U+2013> 'Love the Way You Lie' (Germany single)|publisher=Amazon.com (Germany)|date=September 9, 2009|accessdate=September 10, 2010|language=German}}</ref>

"Love the Way You Lie" received generally favorable reviews. An editor for ''[[Rap-Up (magazine)|Rap-Up]]'' listed it among the four best tracks from the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2010/06/21/review-roundup-eminem-recovery/|title=Review Roundup&nbsp;<U+2013> Eminem&nbsp;<U+2013> 'Recovery'|work=Rap-Up|publisher=Devin Lazerine|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636RExNjD|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no|date=June 21, 2010}}</ref> ''The New York Times'' writer Jon Caramanica considered it "one of the album's most engaging songs" and praised Eminem's ability to assess issues from the perspectives of both sexes.<ref name=nyjon>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/15/arts/music/15jayz.html|first=Jon|last=Caramanica|title=Masters of Triumph and Pain, With Help From Friends|work=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=September 14, 2010|accessdate=December 22, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/64t5ex2QW|archivedate=December 22, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> MTV's Rodriguez wrote that the song echoes content from Eminem's earlier albums, but finds him "sober" and "more mature".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1641932/eminems-recovery-track-by-track-guide.jhtml|first=Jayson|last=Rodriguez|title=Eminem's Recovery: A Track-By-Track Guide|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=June 21, 2010|accessdate=October 7, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6BEd9GWy8|archivedate=October 7, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> He added that the lyrics allude to Eminem's relationship with Scott and that "Love the Way You Lie" is his closest approach to a love song.<ref name="leak">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1641027/eminem-rihanna-lament-abusive-relationship-love-way-lie.jhtml|first=Jayson|last=Rodriguez|title=Eminem, Rihanna Lament Abusive Relationship In 'Love The Way You Lie'|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=June 8, 2010|accessdate=July 31, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62F7EL65g|archivedate=October 6, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Editors of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' compared the single with "Kim" and {{" '}}97 Bonnie & Clyde"; they found he is more tempered in "Love the Way You Lie" when discussing a "mutually destructive relationship" and that Rihanna's involvement creates an eerie mood.<ref name="avclub">{{cite news|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/the-hits-keep-coming-30-songs-inspired-by-domestic,57741/|first1=Vadim|last1=Rizov|first2=Erik|last2=Adams|first3=Sam|last3=Adams|first4=Marcus|last4=Gilmer|first5=Scott|last5=Gordon|first6=Jason|last6=Heller|first7=Genevieve|last7=Koski|first8=Michaelangelo et al|last8=Matos|title=The hits keep coming: 30 songs inspired by domestic violence|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|publisher=[[The Onion]]|accessdate=January 16, 2012}}</ref>

Critics especially praised Rihanna's contribution. Michael Menachem of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' complimented her "exquisitely melodic and surprisingly hopeful" vocal performance and "Eminem's dark, introspective" rapping.<ref name="bill">{{cite web|first=Michael|last=Menachem|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1068964/eminem-feat-rihanna-love-the-way-you-lie |title=Eminem feat. Rihanna, 'Love the Way You Lie' |work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=July 23, 2010 |accessdate=September 10, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Dyx2wbtG|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> He noted that the percussion compliments both artists and that Alex da Kid gave the classical arrangement a mainstream touch.<ref name="bill" /> Kyle Anderson, writing for MTV, wrote that the song showcases Rihanna's emotional vocals and Eminem's "most intense rhymes about his tumultuous relationships".<ref name="MTV dark" /> He regarded "Love the Way You Lie" as an honest, "well-constructed pop song with a killer hook" and likened the "slow-burning" music to that of "[[Someone Like You (Adele song)|Someone Like You]]", a 2011 single by British singer [[Adele (singer)|Adele]].<ref name="MTV dark" /><ref name=sly>{{cite web|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2011/09/14/adele-someone-like-you-first-ballad-hot-100/|first=Kyle|last=Anderson|title=Adele's 'Someone Like You' is the first ballad in three years to top the Hot 100&nbsp;<U+2013> or is it?|work=Entertainment Weekly|publisher=Time Inc|date=September 14, 2011|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> The ''[[Houston Chronicle]]'' pop critic [[Joey Guerra]] commented that Rihanna brought a "sandpaper and silk sheen" to the track.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.chron.com/peep/2010/06/eminem-makes-a-compelling-recovery/|first=Joey|last=Guerra|authorlink=Joey Guerra|title=Eminem makes a compelling ''Recovery''|work=[[Houston Chronicle]]|publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]]|date=June 21, 2010|accessdate=October 10, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62KSB2jnY|archivedate=October 10, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref>

===Themes===
[[File:Chris Brown 2, 2012.jpg|thumb|right|Many critics believed the song was about Rihanna's past relationship with [[Chris Brown (American singer)|Chris Brown]].|alt=Chris Brown wears a sleeveless purple shirt and a pink hat. He has tattooed arms and he holds a microphone with his right hand, facing to the left.]]
Critics and experts have commented on the message in the lyrics. Anderson noted a dark theme,<ref name="MTV dark">{{cite web|url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2010/12/06/eminem-rihanna-love-the-way-you-lie-2010/|first=Kyle|last=Anderson|title=Eminem's 'Love The Way You Lie': Darkness, Liberating Me|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=December 6, 2010|accessdate=July 28, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62GWrVQGn|archivedate=October 7, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> while Nick Levine of [[Digital Spy]], Allie Townsend of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine, and Jocelyn Noveck of [[The Associated Press]] suggested the previous relationships of both artists influenced the song.<ref name=asspress/><ref name="dspy">{{cite web|first=Nick|last=Levine|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a258647/eminem-ft-rihanna-love-the-way-you-lie.html |title=Music&nbsp;<U+2013> Singles Review&nbsp;<U+2013> Eminem ft. Rihanna: 'Love The Way You Lie' |work={{noitalic|Digital Spy}}|publisher=Hachette Filipacchi M<U+00E9>dias|date=August 30, 2010 |accessdate=September 10, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636QxyFGQ|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="timemag">{{cite web|url=http://newsfeed.time.com/2010/08/19/love-the-way-you-lie-7-beloved-violent-songs/|first=Allie|last=Townsend|title=Love The Way You Lie: 7 Beloved Violent Songs|work=Time|publisher=Time Inc|date=August 19, 2010|accessdate=November 5, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/634khSCAg|archivedate=November 9, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Levine gave it four stars out of five.<ref name=dspy/> According to Eric Hayden of [[The Atlantic Wire]], the song refers to an alcoholic couple, possibly inspired by Rihanna's relationship with Brown.<ref name="taw">{{cite web|url=http://www.theatlanticwire.com/entertainment/2010/08/love-the-way-you-lie-what-s-eminem-trying-to-say/23424/|first=Erik|last=Hayden|title=Love the Way You Lie: What's Eminem Trying To Say?|work={{noitalic|[[The Atlantic Wire]]}}|publisher=Atlantic Media Company|date=August 9, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62GX21MJx|archivedate=October 7, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> McAlphine awarded "Love the Way You Lie" four stars out of five.<ref name=bbc/> According to him, the song would not have been effective if it had featured only Eminem's point of view and feelings of regret; he wrote that Rihanna's representing the opposite side of the relationship shows "proper storytelling" and "sends a message" because of her breakup with Brown.<ref name="bbc">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/chartblog/2010/07/emimem_ft_rihanna_love_the_way.shtml|first=Fraser|last=McAlpine|date=July 14, 2010|title=Eminem ft. Rihanna&nbsp;<U+2013> 'Love The Way You Lie'|work={{noitalic|[[BBC Online]]}}|publisher=BBC|accessdate=July 31, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636R4nekw|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> McAlphine wrote that as a result the song depicts a more realistic abusive relationship and could be featured in a campaign for [[women's shelter]]s. He praised Eminem's accuracy and understanding of the topic.<ref name=bbc/> Winston Robbins from the music website [[Consequence of Sound]] attributed the song's poignancy to Rihanna's past abusive relationship, and a theme of infidelity and abuse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2010/06/album-review-eminem-recovery/|first=Winston|last=Robbins|title=Album Review: Eminem&nbsp;<U+2013> ''Recovery''|work={{noitalic|[[Consequence of Sound]]}}|publisher=Alex Young|date=June 25, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636RC6yk1|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref>

On the critical side, ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'''s Jenny McCartney dismissed the metaphors in the chorus and thought that the song's topic was over-hyped.<ref name="tel">{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/columnists/jennymccartney/7957505/Emimen-and-Rihannas-brutality-chic-is-a-bit-beyond-me.html|first=Jenny|last=McCartney|title=Emimen and Rihanna's brutality chic is a bit beyond me|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]]|date=August 21, 2010|accessdate=December 20, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DaqbwypU|archivedate=January 11, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> She disagreed with the critical praise, arguing that women accept abusive relationships for deeper reasons than sexual and emotional pleasure, such as family and financial issues and helplessness.<ref name=tel/> In an [[NPR]] article, the writer [[Maura Johnston]] commented that the lyrics portray Rihanna as the subject of Eminem's violence.<ref name=smoothjohnston>{{Cite web|url=http://www.npr.org/blogs/therecord/2010/08/03/128960713/pop-off-is-the-new-duet-a-dude-rapping-on-a-woman-s-pop-song|first1=Maura|last1=Johnston|first2=Jay|last2=Smooth|title=Pop Off: He Raps, She Sings. Does It Still Count As A Duet?|publisher=[[NPR]]. National Public Radio|date=August 4, 2010|accessdate=December 20, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6BEaXqeb7|archivedate=October 7, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> [[Jay Smooth]], a New York [[radio personality]], responded that  "while Eminem explores the psyche of the abuser with an almost disturbing amount of depth and detail," Rihanna's perspective is downplayed and not explained fully.<ref name=smoothjohnston/> Johnston and Smooth wrote that such imbalances are a prevalent issue in [[popular music]] duets.<ref name=smoothjohnston/> To Sady Doyle, although "Love the Way You Lie" is one of Eminem's most affecting tracks and finds him remorseful, it does not make up for his past [[misogyny|misogynistic]] actions and hateful songs.<ref name="atlantic">{{cite web|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2010/08/why-love-the-way-you-lie-does-not-redeem-eminem/61641/|title=Why 'Love the Way You Lie' Does Not Redeem Eminem|first=Sady|last=Doyle|work=[[The Atlantic]]|publisher=[[Atlantic Media Company]]|date=August 18, 2010|accessdate=August 6, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636RKoNEH|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> 

Noveck questioned whether the lyrics are "a treatise against (or apology for) domestic violence, or an irresponsible glorification of it? Or, is it something uncomfortable in between?"<ref name=asspress/> Marjorie Gilberg, executive director of the anti-teenage violence group Break the Cycle, commented that "Love the Way You Lie" can teach listeners about the dangers of abusive relationships if interpreted correctly. She believed that because popular culture often depicts what is socially acceptable, people may accept such violence more easily. She added, "One problem, though,&nbsp;... is that the song reflects myths about domestic violence<U+2014>myths that lead to blaming the victim."<ref name=asspress/> Gilberg said the victim is often accused of being as guilty as the partner but wants to be loved, not abused.<ref name=asspress/>

===Recognition===
"Love the Way You Lie" ranked in various best-of-2010 lists. Claire Suddath of ''Time'' placed it at number five on her top-ten list and wrote, "That this song didn't come across sounding clich<U+00E9>d or tasteless is a testament to both artists' skill."<ref name="timetop10" /> [[AOL Radio]] considered the song the best of 2010 hip hop music, regarding Eminem as imaginative and passionate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aolradioblog.com/2010/07/10/top-hip-hop-songs-2010/|author=AOL Radio Staff|title=Top Hip-Hop Songs of 2010|work={{noitalic|[[AOL Radio]]}}|publisher=[[AOL]]|accessdate=October 4, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636RTjiRL|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> It ranked ninth on MTV News' top-twenty-five list.<ref name="top102010" >{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1653618/eminems-love-way-lie-mtv-news-9-song-2010.jhtml|first=James|last=Montgomery|title=Eminem's 'Love The Way You Lie' Is MTV News' #9 Song Of 2010|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=December 6, 2010|accessdate=November 23, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/63Q0mChEw|archivedate=November 23, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Its editor James Montgomery attributed the song's success to its theme and relation to the artists' past abusive relationships.<ref name="top102010" /> He concluded, "You cannot write a song any better than that, because that's how this kind of thing happens in real life."<ref name="top102010" /> ''[[New York Post|The New York Post]]'' placed the song at second place on their "top 210 songs from 2010" list and regarded it as a "comeback club anthem."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/music/the_top_songs_from_rcP1AYqcPRebO9oEPN998H|title=The top 210 songs from 2010|work=[[New York Post|The New York Post]]|publisher=[[News Corporation]]|date=December 27, 2010|accessdate=November 29, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/63ZM8grHD|archivedate=November 29, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> In April 2011, Gabriel Alvarez of ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' magazine ranked it at number 100 on their "100 Best Eminem Songs" list, calling it a love song and praising Rihanna's vocals as beautiful.<ref name="complextop100">{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2011/04/the-100-best-eminem-songs/eminem-f-rihanna-love-the-way-you-lie#gallery|first=Gabriel|last=Alvarez|title=The 100 Best Eminem Songs|page=1|date=April 26, 2011|accessdate=October 4, 2011|work=Complex|publisher=Complex Media|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636RWtZgw|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> "Love the Way You Lie" and its accompanying music video were nominated for five [[Grammy Awards]] at the [[2011 Grammy Awards|2011 ceremony]], including "[[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]]", "[[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]" and "[[Grammy Award for Best Short Form Music Video|Best Short Form Music Video]]".<ref name="grammy"/> It won the [[People's Choice Awards]] for "Favorite Music Video" and "Favorite Song".<ref name="peopleschoice"/>

==Commercial performance==
"Love the Way You Lie" reached number one on several [[record chart]]s worldwide.<ref name="sc_Australia_Eminem feat. Rihanna" /> It entered the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number two in the issue dated July 10, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2010-07-10/hot-100|title=Hot 100: Week of July 10, 2010|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=July 10, 2010|accessdate=October 2, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Dyz2cCq2|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> The single debuted at number one on the US [[Hot 100 Digital (Digital Songs)|Digital Songs]] after selling 338,000&nbsp;digital copies in its first week.<ref name=holdoff>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/957555/katy-perry-holds-off-eminem-atop-hot-100|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=July 1, 2010|title=Katy Perry Holds Off Eminem Atop Hot 100|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=July 2, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Dyz8vh5q|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> From July 31 to September 11, 2010, it had a seven-week run at the top of the Hot 100,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/951892/rihanna-and-eminems-love-the-way-you-lie-part-ii-sequel-leaks|first=Monica|last=Herrera|title=Rihanna and Eminem's 'Love the Way You Lie (Part II)' Sequel Leaks|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=November 3, 2010|accessdate=February 1, 2013|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6E7E7btae|archivedate=February 1, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> giving Eminem his fourth, and Rihanna her seventh, number-one US hit.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pietroluongo |first=Silvio |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/957270/eminem-and-rihanna-replace-katy-perry-atop-hot-100 |title=Eminem and Rihanna Replace Katy Perry Atop Hot 100 |work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=July 21, 2010 |accessdate=July 21, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DyzHPluo|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> The single sold more than 300,000&nbsp;digital copies in the week of August 14, 2010, rising to number two on the Pop Songs and [[Radio Songs (Billboard chart)|Radio Songs]] charts.<ref name="airplaygainer">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/957022/eminem-and-rihanna-lie-still-atop-hot-100|first=Silvio|last=Pietroluongo|date=August 5, 2010|title=Eminem and Rihanna Lie 'Still' Atop Hot 100|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=August 11, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DyzOVh1p|archivedate=January 27, 2013}}</ref> In the ''Billboard'' issue for August 21, 2010, [[Nielsen Broadcast Data Systems]] recognized the single with the BDS Certified Award for 50,000&nbsp;radio [[Spin (radio)|spin]]s.<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Nielsen Broadcast Data Systems: BDSCertified Spin Awards July 2010 Recipients|date=August 21, 2010|journal=Billboard|volume=122|issue=33|page=22|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|issn=0006-2510|editor-first=Danyel|editor-last=Smith}}</ref> It topped the Pop Songs chart in the same issue,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2010-08-21/pop-songs|title=Pop Songs: Week of August 21, 2010|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=August 21, 2010|accessdate=March 18, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DyzRUPVw|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> giving Eminem his third number-one track on the chart and Rihanna her sixth.<ref name="BB-PopTies">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/956952/rihanna-ties-for-most-pop-songs-no-1s|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=August 10, 2010|title=Rihanna Ties For Most Pop Songs No. 1s|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=August 9, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DyzWuEPg|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> "Love the Way You Lie" was the first number-one hit on the [[Hot Rap Songs|Rap Songs]] chart with Eminem as the lead artist since his 2000 single "[[The Real Slim Shady]]".<ref name="billboard eminem august">{{cite web|last=Trust|first=Gary|title=Ask ''Billboard'': Eminem's Multi-Chart Domination|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/956621/ask-billboard-eminems-multi-chart-domination |work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=January 29, 2011|date=August 27, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DyzacuN6|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref>

The song entered the [[ARIA Charts|Australian Singles Chart]] on July 4, 2010, at number fourteen.<ref name="sc_Australia_Eminem feat. Rihanna" /> It rose to the top three weeks later, occupying the position for six weeks and staying on the chart for thirty-eight weeks in total.<ref name="sc_Australia_Eminem feat. Rihanna" /> In Austria, "Love the Way You Lie" made its debut at number thirty-one, on July 2, 2010, and ascended to number one on September 4.<ref name="sc_Austria_Eminem feat. Rihanna" /> After making a final consecutive appearance on the chart on March 4,  2011, it reappeared at number 75 on August 26. The song spent forty-seven weeks on the chart.<ref name="sc_Austria_Eminem feat. Rihanna" /> "Love the Way You Lie" stayed on France's singles chart for twenty-three weeks.<ref name="sc_French_Eminem feat. Rihanna" /> Although it never reached the top there, the single's debut and peak position was number three, at which it appeared on July 2, 2010.<ref name="sc_French_Eminem feat. Rihanna" />

By the end of the year, 854,000&nbsp;copies were sold in the UK, making "Love the Way You Lie" the [[List of best-selling singles by year (UK)|country's biggest-selling song of 2010]].<ref name="official charts end of 2010">{{cite web|title=Eminem/Rihanna & Take That scoop 2010 crowns|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/chart-news/cardle-at-no-1-again-eminemrihanna-take-that-scoop-2010-crowns/|publisher=[[The Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=January 29, 2011|date=January 2, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636SFuSqZ|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> In October 2011, it became the 109th song to reach one&nbsp;million sales there.<ref name="The Official Charts Company">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/chart-news/eminem-and-rihanna-clock-up-a-million-sales/|title=Eminem and Rihanna clock up a million sales|publisher=The Official Charts Company|date=October 18, 2011|accessdate=October 18, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636SJF0o3|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> By November 2012, it had sold 1.05&nbsp;million copies in the UK, placing at number 100 on the [[Official Charts Company]]'s "The Million Sellers" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-million-sellers-the-uks-biggest-ever-selling-singles-revealed-1685/|title=The Million Sellers <U+2013> the UK<U+2019>s biggest ever selling singles revealed!|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|last=Lane|first=Dan|date=November 16, 2012|accessdate=November 16, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6CECrCLiO|archivedate=November 16, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> With sales of 4,245,000 copies, "Love the Way You Lie" was the third-best-selling single of 2010 in the US.<ref name="nielsen">{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110106006565/en/Nielsen-Company-Billboard%E2%80%99s-2010-Music-Industry-Report|title=The Nielsen Company & Billboard's 2010 Music Industry Report|work=[[Business Wire]]|publisher=[[Nielsen Business Media]]|date=January 6, 2011|accessdate=August 2, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636SXCNyL|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> It was South Korea's third-best-selling song in 2010 by a foreign artist, with 1,200,653&nbsp;downloads.<ref name="southkorea">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/total/2010.list.gaon|title=2010<U+B144> <U+B514><U+C9C0><U+D138> <U+C885><U+D569>|language=Korean|trans_title=2010 Digital Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|work={{noitalic|[[Gaon Chart]]}}|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636SNwAXf|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}} ''Note: To see sales info, click the <U+B2E4><U+C6B4><U+B85C><U+B4DC> tab and then select <U+C678><U+AD6D> for foreign sales numbers.'' Retrieved March 21, 2011.</ref> According to the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]], it sold 9.3&nbsp;million copies worldwide in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.com/content/section_resources/dmr2011.html|title=IFPI publishes Digital Music Report 2011|publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|date=January 20, 2011|accessdate=February 15, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/636Sb7TCl|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> In December 2011, "Love the Way You Lie" was certified as Eminem's best-selling single.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bet.com/news/music/2011/12/02/eminem-outdoes-himself-with-love-the-way-you-lie.html|first=N. Jamiyla|last=Chisholm|title=Eminem Outdoes Himself With 'Love The Way You Lie'|work={{noitalic|[[Black Entertainment Television]]}}|publisher=[[BET Networks]]|date=December 2, 2011|accessdate=December 18, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Dyx2wbtG|archivedate=January 27, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> By July 2013, it had sold 5,939,000 copies in the US.<ref name="yahoo 2013">{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-july-21-2013-songs-dancing-miley-201711611.html|title=Week Ending July 21, 2013. Songs: Dancing With Miley|work={{noitalic|Chart Watch}}|publisher=Yahoo|last=Grein|first=Paul|date=July 21, 2013|accessdate=August 12, 2013|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6IpaSH4mO|archivedate=August 12, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref>

==Music video==

===Production===
[[File:MeganFoxSept10TIFF.jpg|thumb|upright=0.6|The actress [[Megan Fox]], according to the director Joseph Kahn, helped the video have a strong impact.|alt=A shot of Megan Fox from the chest up, with dark brown hair.]]
The music video for "Love the Way You Lie" was Eminem's third to be directed by the American filmmaker [[Joseph Kahn]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1643919/eminem-rihanna-shoot-love-way-lie-video-on-tuesday.jhtml|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|title=Eminem, Rihanna To Shoot 'Love The Way You Lie' Video On Tuesday|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=July 19, 2010|accessdate=January 1, 2013|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DNTjMPM2|archivedate=January 2, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> Despite having planned to shoot a [[feature film]] and stop directing pop videos, Kahn chose to work on "Love the Way You Lie" because, according to him, the song discusses an important topic.<ref name="giant">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1645663/love-way-lie-director-knew-eminem-video-would-be-giant.jhtml|first=James|last=Montgomery|title='Love The Way You Lie' Director Knew Eminem Video Would Be 'Giant'|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 12, 2010|accessdate=August 3, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/63791MYPc|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> This was an opportunity for him to direct a video for Eminem without the comedic themes of their previous collaborations.<ref name="vibe" /> For the video, Kahn considered the English actor [[Dominic Monaghan]] as a co-star for his versatility, which he thought would help him play an antagonist.<ref name="lieshoot">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1645755/eminems-lie-video-shoot-was-like-acting-workshop-director.jhtml|first=James|last=Montgomery|title=Eminem's 'Lie' Video Shoot Was Like An Acting Workshop, Director Says|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 13, 2010|accessdate=September 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/637981Fxc|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Kahn cast the American actress [[Megan Fox]], which he had presumed would be almost impossible because of her popularity with directors.<ref name="vibe">{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe.com/posts/love-way-you-lie-director-joseph-kahn-says-megan-fox-plays-key-role-video|author=MikeyFresh|title='Love The Way You Lie' Director: 'Megan <nowiki>[</nowiki>Fox<nowiki>]</nowiki> Was The Key'|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|publisher=[[InterMedia Partners]]|date=August 12, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/637941EwF|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Fox, a fan of Eminem, accepted the role unhesitatingly.<ref name="vibe" />

Rosenberg gave Kahn one&nbsp;day to write a [[Film treatment|treatment]], which Kahn finished in forty-five&nbsp;minutes.<ref name="vibe" /> He filmed Eminem's and Rihanna's parts on July 20, 2010;<ref name="wrap">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1645037/eminems-love-way-lie-video-premieres-thursday-on-mtv.jhtml|first=Kara|last=Warner|title=Eminem's 'Love The Way You Lie' Video Premieres Thursday On MTV|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 4, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6379Bc4BD|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> scenes with Fox and Monaghan were shot three days later.<ref name="MTV-kissing"/> By July 24, 2010, they had finished the shoot.<ref name="tweetkahn">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1644394/eminem-rihanna-video-premiere-sometime-this-week.jhtml|first=Kyle|last=Anderson|title=Eminem, Rihanna Video To Premiere Sometime This Week|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=July 26, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6379N2wRQ|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Kahn confirmed the completion of the [[director's cut]] the next day.<ref name="wrap" /> He said Fox's involvement made the video powerful,<ref name="vibe" /> commenting for ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]'':

<blockquote>
We wanted to make a specific story about two people<U+2014>Meg and Dom<U+2014>not a video that was representative of all couples or all domestic violence situations. I'm not saying that all couples fight this way. I just want people just to be able to identify with the characters and recognize that they've seen relationships like this where two people are together that are completely wrong for each other and things spiral out of control.&nbsp;... Megan was the key to this video.&nbsp;... I'll tell you as a director the reason why [Fox and Monaghan's] scenes in the video feel so real is because in the moment they were real.<ref name="vibe" />
</blockquote>

Monaghan told MTV he thought the couple represents Eminem and Scott.<ref name="howdid">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1657528/grammy-eminem-love-the-way-you-lie.jhtml|first=Jayson|last=Rodriguez|title=Eminem's Grammy-Nominated 'Love The Way You Lie': How Did It Happen?|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=2011-0-09|accessdate=July 28, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ABAEllmw|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> The clip was produced by Kathy Angstadt and Maryann Tanedo of HSI Productions.<ref name="mmva" /> Shortly before its release, Eminem reported in a press statement: "Joseph and I worked pretty closely together to make sure we got this right".<ref name=EminemVideo/> He said the difficult topic resulted in a powerful video because of the contributions of Rihanna, Fox and Monaghan.<ref name="EminemVideo">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/eminem/233061-eminem-rihanna-love-the-way-you-lie-video|title=Eminem Talks Love The Way You Lie Video|work=''[[MTV (UK and Ireland)|MTV UK]]''|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 5, 2010|accessdate=July 28, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6379WCjeP|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Fox donated her appearance fee to the Soujourn House, a battered women's shelter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/perfect-couples/eminen-and-rihannas-love-the-way-you-lie-video-debuts_article_35414|title=Eminen & Rihanna's 'Love The Way You Lie' Video Debuts|work=Access Hollywood|publisher=NBC|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6379awUMG|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> On August 5, 2010, the video premiered on MTV and the music video website [[Vevo]].<ref name="wrap" /><ref name="abuse">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/957009/eminem-tackles-abuse-in-love-the-way-you-lie-clip|first=Mariel|last=Concepcion|title=Eminem Tackles Abuse In 'Love The Way You Lie' Clip|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=August 5, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011}}</ref>

===Synopsis===
[[File:Love the way you lie video.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.4|Eminem and Rihanna stand in front of a burning house in the video. The ''[[Daily Mail]]'' wrote that the fire is an important symbol in the clip.<ref name=symbolfire>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1300782/Love-The-Way-You-Lie-Dominic-Monaghan-calls-Megan-Fox-right-kisser-raunchy-video-released.html|title=Megan Fox branded an 'all right' kisser by Dominic Monaghan as raunchy video is released|work=[[Daily Mail]]|publisher=Daily Mail and General Trust|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=September 2, 2013|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6JKnIzIsO|archivedate=September 2, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref>|alt=Rihanna and Eminem are standing in front of a burning house in a dark setting.]]
Rihanna sings the chorus in front of a burning house, while an interspersing scene shows fire on a woman's (Fox) palms. In another scene, the woman is asleep with her lover (Monaghan) and wakes up. Eminem begins to rap in an open field. The woman attacks her lover after seeing the name "Cindy" and a phone number written on his hand.<ref name="onfire" /> He unsuccessfully tries to kiss the woman and brings her back after she attempts to leave him. The man then pushes her onto the wall and aims his fist at her, puncturing the wall instead. After Rihanna sings again, the video [[flashback (narrative)|flashes back]] to when the couple first meet "at a seedy dive bar next door" to a liquor store.<ref name="MTV-kissing">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1644411/megan-fox-dominic-monaghan-caught-kissing-eminem-video.jhtml|first=James|last=Montgomery|date=July 26, 2010|title=Megan Fox, Dominic Monaghan Caught Kissing For Eminem Video&nbsp;<U+2013> News Story|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|accessdate=August 7, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/637AFoZwV|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="onfire">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1645217/eminem-rihannas-love-way-lie-video-love-on-fire.jhtml|first=Shaheem|last=Reid|title=Eminem And Rihanna's 'Love The Way You Lie' Video: Love On Fire|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 5, 2010|accessdate=July 31, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/637A9X2K0|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> The man steals a bottle of [[vodka]] and they kiss on the rooftop.<ref name="okmag">{{cite web|url=http://www.okmagazine.com/2010/08/video-eminem-rihannas-love-the-way-you-lie-music-video/|first=Britanny|last=Talarico|title=VIDEO: Eminem & Rihanna's 'Love The Way You Lie' Music Video|work=[[OK!]]|publisher=[[Northern & Shell]]|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=July 31, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/637AJ8EIA|archivedate=November 11, 2011}}</ref>

During the present, the man apologizes to his lover and they are reconciled. In another flashback, he attacks someone who plays [[Pool (cue sports)|pool]] with his lover.<ref name="onfire" /> Eminem joins Rihanna in front of the burning house for the final verse. Meanwhile, after the flashback, the woman comes home and locks herself in the bathroom to stop her abusive lover from entering. In another scene, the fire on her palms vanish as she clasps her hands. Flames later engulf Eminem and the couple,<ref name="wsj">{{cite news|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2010/08/05/love-the-way-you-lie-video-eminem-and-rihanna-team-up-video/|first=Jozen|last=Cummings|date=August 5, 2010|title='Love the Way You Lie' Video: Eminem and Rihanna Team Up|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|publisher=[[Dow Jones & Company]]|accessdate=October 2, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/637ANSJbp|archivedate=November 11, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> who are then shown fighting in front of the burning house. In the end, the couple stay together and the video returns to their first scene, in which they sleep.<ref name="onfire" /><ref name="boston">{{Cite news|url=http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/editorial_opinion/editorials/articles/2010/09/15/rihanna_violence_isnt_passion/|title=Rihanna: Violence isn't passion|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=September 15, 2010|accessdate=October 10, 2011}}</ref>
{{-}}

===Reception===
{{Quote box|width=30%|align=right|quote="It's the story of them getting to know each other, and it's the story of their tumultuous relationship, and it was the story of the breakdown of their relationship. Ultimately, what I think [Eminem]'s trying to say in the song&nbsp;... is that he should have walked away a little bit quicker than he did and not let it get as messy as it did."|source=<U+2014>Monaghan's interpretation of "Love the Way You Lie"<ref name="nilva" />}}

The clip broke what was a [[YouTube]] record at the time of its release for the most hits in one day, with 6.6&nbsp;million,<ref name="DS-BreakRecord">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a258634/eminem-and-rihanna-break-youtube-record.html|title=Music &ndash; News &ndash; Eminem and Rihanna break YouTube record|work=Digital Spy|publisher=Hachette Filipacchi M<U+00E9>dias|first=Robert|last=Copsey|date=2010-08-09|accessdate=2011-07-31|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/63JTvGjqY|archivedate=2011-11-19|deadurl=no}}</ref> and is [[List of most viewed YouTube videos|the site's fourth-most viewed video]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youtube.com/charts/videos_views?gl=US&t=a|title=Charts|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=July 19, 2013}}</ref> It had a mixed reception from critics, most of whom commented on scenes of domestic violence.<ref name=top10pop/> NPR's Zoe Chace deemed the video sickening,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.npr.org/blogs/therecord/2010/08/06/129026488/-love-the-way-you-lie-video-drops|first=Zoe|last=Chace|title=New Eminem And Rihanna Video: A Bad Situation Getting Worse|publisher=NPR. National Public Radio|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AB9t7Ikh|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> while [[AOL Music]] listed it at number&nbsp;five on their list of the "Top 10 Most Controversial Music Videos in Pop".<ref name="top10pop">{{cite web|url=http://blog.music.aol.ca/2011/09/29/controversial-music-videos/|first=Contessa|last=Gayles|title=Top 10 Most Controversial Music Videos in Pop|work={{noitalic|AOL Music}}|publisher=AOL|date=September 29, 2011|accessdate=October 7, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/63JU4JYbu|archivedate=November 19, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> Stephanie Nilva<U+2014>the executive director of trauma resource center Day One<U+2014>told MTV News that it mainly raises "the topic of dating violence among young people".<ref name=nilva/> Nilva praised the clip's accurate depiction of patterns in an abusive relationship and thought the video's potency came from Eminem's history of violence-themed songs and Brown's assault on Rihanna.<ref name="nilva">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1645285/eminems-love-way-lie-warns-cycle-abuse.jhtml|first=Rochell|last=Thomas|coauthors=Murphy, Adam|title=Eminem's 'Love The Way You Lie' Warns Of The Cycle Of Abuse|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/63JU7pVjg|archivedate=November 19, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref>

A writer for ''Rap-Up'' considered the video realistic, as "art imitates life".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2010/08/05/video-eminem-f-rihanna-love-the-way-you-lie/|title=Video: Eminem f/ Rihanna&nbsp;<U+2013> 'Love the Way You Lie'|work=Rap-Up|publisher=Devin Lazerine|date=August 5, 2010|accessdate=October 15, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnF5toB|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Conor Friedersdorf of ''The Atlantic'' called it an inaccurate portrayal of domestic violence due to insufficient violence, as evidenced by the lack of injuries after punching through a wall.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/daily-dish/archive/2010/08/-love-the-way-you-lie/182962/|first=Conor|last=Friedersdorf|title='Love the Way You Lie'|work=The Atlantic|publisher=Atlantic Media Company|date=August 31, 2010|accessdate=September 1, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AMUtJhTR|archivedate=September 1, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Mariel Concepcion of ''Billboard'' suggested the video was inspired by the lyric,<ref name="abuse" /> "Just gonna stand there and watch me burn, but that's alright because I like the way it hurts."<ref name=lyricnotes/> Rihanna's appearance was criticized. Writing for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine, Daniel Kreps called it "especially striking" and noted her relationship with Brown.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/kanye-west-eminem-unleash-new-videos-20100806|title=Kanye West, Eminem Unleash New Videos|work=Rolling Stone|publisher=Wenner Media|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=August 7, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AB9yEs9k|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> An editor from ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' commented that although the video is realistic, it hinders Rihanna's ability to set an example for women in abusive relationships.<ref name="boston" /> President Terry O'Neill of the [[National Organization for Women]] said the singer unintentionally glorifies domestic violence.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1301058/Is-Rihanna-glorifying-domestic-violence-Victim-stars-controversial-Emimem-music-video.html|title=Is Rihanna glorifying domestic violence? Victim stars in controversial Emimem music video|work=Daily Mail|publisher=Daily Mail and General Trust|date=August 7, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ABA7MwxH|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref>

Brittany Talarico of ''[[OK!]]'' magazine saw the video's message as significant to both artists.<ref name="okmag" /> Billy Johnson Jr. from [[Yahoo! Music]] wrote that Fox's character alternated between vulnerable and confrontational personalities, while Monaghan's character is similar to Eminem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/hip-hop-media-training/megan-fox-and-dominic-monaghan-brawl-in-eminems-love-the-way-you-lie-video.html|first=Billy|last=Johnson Jr.|title=Megan Fox And Dominic Monaghan Brawl In Eminem's 'Love The Way You Lie' Video|work={{noitalic|Yahoo! Music}}|publisher=Yahoo!|date=August 5, 2010|accessdate=July 28, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ABAB9H51|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Kahn, who understood why viewers thought Eminem's and Rihanna's relationships influenced the video, asked that they realize this is untrue. He said the team had been conscious of such personal matters and Fox's and Monaghan's characters are only significant to each other.<ref name="notreal">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1645470/love-way-lie-video-not-about-eminem-rihanna.jhtml|first=James|last=Montgomery|title='Love The Way You Lie' Video Is 'Not About Eminem Or Rihanna,' Director Says|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 10, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ABAI9qvO|archivedate=August 25, 2012}}</ref>

Reviewers discussed the acting. Peter Gicas of ''[[E! News]]'' noted that Fox and Monaghan portray "combustible behavior the tune is hellbent on describing."<ref name="enews">{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/video_face-off_eminem_vs_kanye_west/194080|first=Peter|last=Gicas|title=Video Face-Off: Eminem vs. Kanye West|work=[[E! News]]|publisher=[[E!]]|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=October 15, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AB9o37QJ|archivedate=August 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> ''The New York Post''{{'}}s Jarett Wieselman wrote that they play their roles perfectly and help make the video powerful.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/blogs/popwrap/megan_fox_is_best_seen_and_not_heard_QqNNwZWbanqrQZmDhbvi2N|first=Jarett|last=Wieselman|title=Megan Fox is best seen and not heard|work=The New York Post|publisher=News Corporation|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=August 14, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnL0bE9|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> ''Entertainment Weekly''{{'}}s Whitney Pastorek found the violent acting sexually appealing,<ref name="Whitney">{{cite web|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2010/08/06/eminem-love-the-way-you-lie-video/|first=Whitney|last=Pastorek|title=Eminem's 'Love the Way You Lie' video: Is this depiction of domestic violence too much?|work=Entertainment Weekly|publisher=Time Inc|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnPworW|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> while Willa Paskin of ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine wrote that the cast's appeal "hypnotize[s]" viewers.<ref name=nycmag/> Paskin noted the use of [[Photographic print toning#Sepia toning|sepia toning]] in the burning-house scenes.<ref name=nycmag>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2010/08/eminems_love_the_way_you_lie_v.html|first=Willa|last=Paskin|title=Eminem's 'Love the Way You Lie' Video Is Not Rihanna's Domestic-Abuse Video|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|publisher=New York Media|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=October 15, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnUbDGD|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Matthew Wilkening of AOL Radio commented that the video leaves viewers to decide "if it's a good thing or a bad thing that the pair always end up reconciling."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aolradioblog.com/2010/08/06/megan-fox-stars-in-eminems-new-love-the-way-you-lie-video/|first=Matthew|last=Wilkening|title=Megan Fox Stars in Eminem's New 'Love the Way You Lie Video'|work={{noitalic|AOL Radio}}|publisher=AOL|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=August 26, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnck89H|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Mikey Fresh of ''Vibe'' commented that Fox's natural reaction when Monaghan pierces the wall and almost hits her is an "incredible act of vulnerability".<ref name="vibe" /> ''[[L Magazine]]''{{'}}s Benjamin Sutton likened the scene in which the characters burn to [[Chris Bradley]], whom Monaghan portrayed in the 2009 action film ''[[X-Men Origins: Wolverine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelmagazine.com/TheMeasure/archives/2010/08/06/thank-goodness-the-eminem-rihanna-megan-fox-video-for-love-the-way-you-lie-is-better-than-power|first=Benjamin|last=Sutton|title=Thank Goodness the Eminem-Rihanna-Megan Fox Video for 'Love The Way You Lie' Is Better Than 'Power'|work=[[L Magazine]]|publisher=Nick Burry|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=October 15, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnhMFeQ|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Mail]]'' wrote that the fire is symbolically important in the video, as it consumes Fox's character.<ref name=symbolfire/>

==Live performances==
[[File:Eminem and Rihanna in Love the Way You Lie2.jpg|thumb|upright=1.3|Eminem and [[Rihanna]] performing "Love the Way You Lie" at [[Electronic Entertainment Expo 2010|E3 2010]]|alt=A large screen with the silhouette of a man, seated with two pistols, is in the center. Surrounding it are screens showing Eminem, who is to the right of Rihanna. The latter is holding a microphone and has short red hair.]]
On June 15, 2010, Eminem and Rihanna performed "Love the Way You Lie" at Los Angeles' [[Electronic Entertainment Expo 2010]], accompanied by the drummer [[Travis Barker]] and [[D12]]'s [[Kon Artis|Mr. Porter]].<ref name="MTVE3">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1641565/eminem-surprises-e3-crowd-with-guests-travis-barker-rihanna.jhtml|first=Matt|last=Elias|title=Eminem Surprises E3 Crowd With Guests Travis Barker, Rihanna|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=June 15, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFnvpIGq|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Eminem sang "Love the Way You Lie" at the Scottish festival [[T in the Park 2010|T in the Park]] on July 10, 2010, dedicating it to "everybody who'[d] been in a fucked-up relationship."<ref name="nme">{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/eminem/51970|title=Eminem plays first European show since 2005 at T In The Park&nbsp;<U+2013> T In The Park Festival News&nbsp;<U+2013> Festivals Guide 2010|date=July 10, 2010|accessdate=August 2, 2011|work=[[NME]]|publisher=[[IPC Media]]|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AFo0ODP1|archivedate=August 28, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> He then performed the song at Ireland's annual [[Oxegen 2010|Oxegen]] festival on July 11, 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/music/news/in-pictures-fans-brave-mud-to-see-eminem-and-black-eyed-peas-at-oxegen-festival-in-punchestown-14873507.html |title=In Pictures: Fans brave mud to see Eminem and Black Eyed Peas at Oxegen festival in Punchestown |work=[[The Belfast Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Independent News and Media]]|date=July 12, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wTbCHV|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> James Hendicott from ''[[State (magazine)|State]]'' wrote that the rapper's personality "fill[ed] the stage" and that his vocals were sharp and packed "plenty of punch".<ref name="state">{{cite web|url=http://www.state.ie/21465-live-reviews/oxegen-2010-eminem|first=James|last=Hendicott|title=Oxegen 2010: Eminem|work=[[State (magazine)|State]]|publisher=Roger Woolman|date=July 12, 2010|accessdate=August 3, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wa1IHI|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> He criticized the use of a pre-recorded backing track and noted the lack of live music and female vocals.<ref name="state" /> Eamon Sweeney from the ''[[Irish Independent]]'' called Eminem's performance only "mildly impressive".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/review-eminem-stands-up-but-hes-no-prodigy-2255939.html|first=Eamon|last=Sweeney|title=Review: Eminem stands up but he's no Prodigy|work=[[Irish Independent]]|publisher=Independent News and Media|date=July 13, 2010|accessdate=July 27, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wemEoU|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 

On July 21, 2010, the rapper joined Rihanna on her [[Last Girl on Earth Tour]] to perform at the [[Staples Center]] in Los Angeles.<ref name="surprise">{{cite news |last=Forbes |first=Sophie |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1296894/Eminem-surprises-Rihanna-fans-LA-concert.html?ito=feeds-newsxml |title=Eminem surprises Rihanna fans at her LA concert |work=Daily Mail |publisher=Daily Mail and General Trust |date=July 23, 2010 |accessdate=July 23, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wnO220|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> He then performed at the [[2010 MTV Video Music Awards]] and was voted the best performer of the ceremony in an MTV poll, earning 34 percent of votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1647652/eminem-kicks-off-vmas-with-surprise-rihanna-cameo.jhtml |first=Gil|last=Kaufman|title=Eminem Kicks Off VMAs With Surprise Rihanna Cameo|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=September 13, 2010|accessdate=September 27, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wrxErd|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/eminem/237548-eminem-rihanna-vmas |title=Eminem And Rihanna's Performance Voted Best Of 2010 VMAs |work={{noitalic|MTV UK}}|publisher=MTV Networks |date=September 15, 2010 |accessdate=October 9, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wvnaLD|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Rihanna made a surprise appearance despite having said she could not perform because of her schedule.<ref name="ewvma">{{cite web|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2010/09/12/eminem-opens-vmas/ |title=Eminem and surprise guest Rihanna open VMAs |work=Entertainment Weekly|publisher=Time Inc|date=September 12, 2010 |accessdate=October 9, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6x2mQL4|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><!--He performed in a black [[jacket]], [[hoodie]] and white [[T-shirt]], while Rihanna wore a white [[Ballet tutu|tutu]] and black [[combat boot]]s.<ref name="ewvma" /> --> Suddath of ''Time'' called their duet dull.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2017751_2017750_2017749,00.html|first=Claire|last=Suddath|title=Eminem: 'Not Afraid' and 'Love the Way You Lie'|work=Time|publisher=Time Inc|date=September 13, 2010|accessdate=November 5, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D6wzokqc|archivedate=December 22, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Eminem sang "Love the Way You Lie" without Rihanna at the 2011 [[Bonnaroo Music Festival]] for almost 80,000 people.<ref name="Bonnaroo">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1665585/eminem-bonnaroo.jhtml|first=James|last=Montgomery|title=Eminem Sets Off Musical Fireworks At Bonnaroo|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=June 12, 2011|accessdate=July 28, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D9Rc3FYn|archivedate=December 24, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="bil" >{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/470584/eminem-rules-bonnaroo-2011-with-fiery-headlining-set|author=Associated Press|title=Eminem Rules Bonnaroo 2011 with Fiery Headlining Set|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=June 12, 2011|accessdate=September 5, 2011}}</ref> According to MTV News' Montgomery, the "sheer tenacity with which he attacked" was his strength.<ref name="Bonnaroo" /> Patrick Doyle of ''Rolling Stone'' felt Eminem delivered a triumphal act by "constantly bouncing across the stage" and singing energetically.<ref name="bonrol">{{cite web|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/blogs/festivals/eminem-buffalo-springfield-rule-bonnaroo-day-three-20110612|first=Patrick|last=Doyle|title=Eminem, Buffalo Springfield Rule Bonnaroo Day Three|work=Rolling Stone|publisher=Wenner Media|date=June 12, 2011|accessdate=September 5, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D9Rf4DvD|archivedate=December 24, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> 

Eminem performed "Love the Way You Lie" on the second day of Chicago's annual Lollapalooza festival on August 6, 2011.<ref name="USA">{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/music/news/2011-08-07-lollapalooza-2011-eminem_n.htm|first=Piet|last=Levy|title=Lollapalooza 2011: Eminem rules Day Two|work=[[USA Today]]|publisher=[[Gannett Company]]|date=August 7, 2011|accessdate=August 9, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6D9RlYxUc|archivedate=December 24, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Piet Levy of ''[[USA Today]]'' named the show a "tragic stunner", as members of the audience sang the chorus to compensate for Rihanna's absence.<ref name=USA/><ref name="Chicago">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1668598/eminem-lollapalooza.jhtml|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|title=Eminem Slays Massive Crowd At Lollapalooza|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 7, 2011|accessdate=August 9, 2011}}</ref> Katie Hasty of [[HitFix]] added that it displayed competition between the sexes.<ref name="HF">{{cite web|url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/immaculate-noise/posts/eminem-joined-by-bruno-mars-skylar-grey-royce-da-59-at-lollapalooza|first=Katie|last=Hasty|title=Eminem joined by Bruno Mars, Skylar Grey, Royce da 5'9" at Lollapalooza|publisher=[[HitFix]]|date=August 7, 2011|accessdate=August 8, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/69tAdhWCJ|archivedate=August 13, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> On August 20, 2011, Eminem and Rihanna performed in [[Staffordshire]] on the first day of V2011 ([[V Festival]])<!--, dressed in a [[denim]] shirt and shorts with [[Fishnet|fishnet stocking]]s, later wearing a black leather dress-->.<ref name="v2011">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/eminem/329348-rihanna-joins-eminem-on-stage-at-v-festival|title=Rihanna Joins Eminem On Stage At V Festival|work={{noitalic|MTV UK}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=August 21, 2011|accessdate=August 21, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDE8KRpL|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> James Lachno of ''The Daily Telegraph'' considered it an "affecting" rendition.<ref name="telegraph">{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-festivals/8716514/V-Festival-Hylands-Park-Chelmsford-review.html|first=James|last=Lachno|title=V Festival, Hylands Park, Chelmsford, review|work=The Daily Telegraph|publisher=Telegraph Media Group|date=August 22, 2011|accessdate=October 11, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDEC5ORP|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'' called their performance thrilling and an editor for the British newspaper ''[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]'' felt that it was the best part of the evening.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2011/aug/21/v-festival-review-rihanna-eminem|first=Chris|last=Salmon|title=V Festival: day one&nbsp;<U+2013> review|work=The Guardian|publisher=Guardian Media Group|date=August 21, 2011|accessdate=August 21, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6C0NpvWxj|archivedate=November 7, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.metro.co.uk/music/872988-eminem-joined-by-rihanna-at-v-festival-for-love-the-way-you-lie|first=Rachel|last=Tarley|title=Eminem joined by Rihanna at V Festival for Love The Way You Lie|work=Metro|publisher=Associated Newspapers|date=August 21, 2011|accessdate=August 21, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDF3C7ow|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Eminem closed the festival on the night of August 21 in [[Chelmsford]], [[Essex]], for an audience of 120,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/14611620|first=Chi Chi|last=Izundu|title=Rapper Eminem closes V Festival at Chelmsford in Essex|work={{noitalic|BBC Online}}|publisher=BBC|date=August 22, 2011|accessdate=August 22, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDF7APj3|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> A reporter for the ''[[International Business Times]]'' thought that Eminem's duet with Rihanna was the highlight of the show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://uk.ibtimes.com/articles/201542/20110822/rihanna-eminem-v-festival-i-love-the-way-u-lie-weston-park.htm|title=Eminem and Rihanna Sizzle at V Festival (Video)|work=[[International Business Times]]|publisher=Etienne Uzac|date=August 22, 2011|accessdate=August 22, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AZRKNb7k|archivedate=September 10, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref>

==Cover versions==
<!-- NOTE: Please do not add covers of this song and use the YouTube link as a source. WP:SONG requires that song covers' notability be established by third party reliable sources. Thanks! -->
Multiple musical acts have performed [[cover version]]s of "Love the Way You Lie". The country music group [[The Band Perry]] sang the song at the June 2010 [[CMT Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1665449/cmt-awards-taylor-swift-justin-bieber-kid-rock.jhtml|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|title=Taylor Swift, Justin Bieber Turn CMT Awards Into Crossover Celebration|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=June 9, 2011|accessdate=January 19, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDEONsuY|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Two months later, [[Taylor Momsen]]<U+2014>the lead singer of the American rock band [[The Pretty Reckless]]<U+2014>performed a cover version for [[BBC Radio 1]]'s ''[[Live Lounge]]'' as part of a [[Mashup (music)|mashup]] with the song "[[Islands (The xx song)|Islands]]" by the English pop band [[The xx]].<ref name=hollywoodrep>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/taylor-momsen-covers-eminem-rihanna-track-says-no-beef-with-pop-singer_article_36153|title=Taylor Momsen Covers Eminem, Rihanna Track, Says No Beef With Pop Singer|work=Access Hollywood|publisher=NBC|date=August 27, 2010|accessdate=January 12, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDESXhmE|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Assisted by a guitarist from her band, she began with a section of "Islands" and transitioned into the chorus of "Love the Way You Lie".<ref name=hollywoodrep/>

[[Cher Lloyd]], a British singer, performed the song in the final five of ''[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor UK]]''{{'}}s [[The X Factor (UK series 7)|seventh season]].<ref name="express.co.uk">{{cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/posts/view/215673/Hype-and-glory-as-X-Factor-final-looms-|first=Mernie|last=Gilmore|title=Hype and glory as X Factor Final looms|work=[[Daily Express]]|publisher=Northern & Shell|date=December 6, 2010|accessdate=December 11, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDEgCSz2|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="mirror">{{Cite news|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/tv/2010/12/04/cher-lloyd-flips-out-twice-on-eve-of-x-factor-semi-finals-115875-22760244/|first1=Mark|last1=Jefferies|first2=Ashleigh|last2=Rainbird|title=X Factor: Cher Lloyd has screaming fit and lashes out at camerawoman, forcing Cheryl Cole to step in|work=Daily Mirror|publisher=Trinity Mirror|date=December 4, 2010|accessdate=September 20, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6AZRRDfvs|archivedate=September 10, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> A writer from ''[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]'' called the performance "stripped-back" and "without any of her usual stage gimmicks."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/tv/x_factor/3260774/They-all-just-need-a-big-Cardle.html|title=They all just need a big Cardle|work=The Sun|publisher=News International|date=December 4, 2010|accessdate=January 12, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDEpyXLy|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Mernie Gilmore of the ''[[Daily Express]]'' commented that the song is "a duet for a reason" as Lloyd performed both Eminem's and Rihanna's parts.<ref name="express.co.uk" /> In 2010, the Russian guitarist [[Alex Feather Akimov]], released "Love The Way You Lie (Heavy Remix)", a recording that was recognized by Billboard.biz (Web Trends).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/news/e3i493aa786b5893edc8145c05a90bceac5|title=Web Trends: The Slits, Eminem, Miley Cyrus and more|first=Megan|last=Vick|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=October 21, 2010|accessdate=August 2, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/62KQ4vUNM|archivedate=October 10, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref> The American [[post-hardcore]] band [[A Skylit Drive]] recorded a cover of the single for ''[[Punk Goes Pop 4]]'', the 2011 release of the ''[[Punk Goes...]]'' series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/punk_goes_pop_volume_4_announced_features_sleeping_with_sirens_go_radio_woe|first=Tyler|last=Common|title=Punk Goes Pop Volume 4 announced, features Sleeping With Sirens, Go Radio, Woe Is Me, and more|work=[[Alternative Press]]|publisher=Alternative Press Magazine|date=September 22, 2011|accessdate=January 21, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/64rRX6bi7|archivedate=January 21, 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref>
