A parody version was produced alongside a music video, titled "Because I'm A Man", for the December 1, 2012, episode of [[Saturday Night Live|Saturday Night Live Korea]], hosted by [[Korean-American]] singer and rapper, [[Jay Park]], resulting in the shows highest ratings of the season.<ref name=snl-mnet>{{cite web|title=Jay Park Brings High Ratings to "SNL Korea"|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=22811|publisher=mnet|accessdate=December 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SNL<U+CF54><U+B9AC><U+C544>, SNL Korea Ep.13 : <U+B0A8><U+C790><U+AE30> <U+B54C><U+BB38><U+C5D0>|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=45rWkju85kQ|publisher=tvN|accessdate=December 25, 2012}}</ref>-->

==Sequel==
{{Main|Love the Way You Lie (Part II)|l1="Love the Way You Lie (Part II)"}}
[[File:Rihanna - Love the Way You Lie Pt. II - Birmingham.jpg|thumb|Rihanna performing "Love the Way You Lie (Part II)" on the [[Loud Tour]] (2011) in Birmingham, England|alt=Rihanna is standing on a grand piano on a stage illuminated with purple light.]]
On November 3, 2010, an alternative version titled "Love the Way You Lie (Part II)" leaked onto the Internet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1651397/rihanna-eminems-love-way-lie-part-ii-leaks.jhtml|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|title=Rihanna And Eminem's 'Love The Way You Lie (Part II)' Leaks|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=November 3, 2010|accessdate=October 16, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFJfhfj|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Rihanna is the lead vocalist and Eminem is a featured guest. The song mainly views matters from Rihanna's perspective and is based on Grey's demo.<ref name="latimesmag">{{cite news|first=Gerrick D.|last=Kennedy|title=Hooked|url=http://www.latimesmagazine.com/2011/06/hooked.html|accessdate=December 4, 2011|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|publisher=[[Tribune Company]]|month=June|year=2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFMsnvN|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1651117/rihanna-initially-against-love-way-lie-part-ii-with-eminem.jhtml|title=Rihanna Initially Against 'Love The Way You Lie (Part II)' With Eminem|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|date=October 29, 2010|accessdate=October 11, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFPd8ed|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Rihanna agreed to record a sequel after initially thinking "the original couldn't be beaten".<ref name="TSun-Worried">{{cite news|url=http://www.torontosun.com/entertainment/music/2010/10/30/15890306-wenn-photo.html|title=Rihanna worried about Eminem duet sequel|date=October 30, 2010|work=[[Toronto Sun]]|publisher=[[Sun Media]]|accessdate=July 31, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFThdbD|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> She said that the sequel involved less production, with only piano and drums.<ref name="TSun-Worried"/> It is the eleventh and final track on her 2010 studio album ''[[Loud (Rihanna album)|Loud]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/rihanna/53516|title=Tracklisting for new Rihanna album 'Loud' revealed online|work=NME|publisher=IPC Media|date=October 21, 2010|accessdate=February 29, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/65p1DU3B7|archivedate=February 29, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Grey's version appears on her 2012 [[extended play]] ''The Buried Sessions of Skylar Grey'' and her 2013 studio album ''[[Don't Look Down (Skylar Grey album)|Don't Look Down]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2012/01/05/skylar-grey-unveils-buried-sessions-artwork/|title=Skylar Grey Unveils 'Buried Sessions' Artwork|work=Rap-Up|publisher=Devin Lazerine|date=January 5, 2012|accessdate=April 18, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/671UCck5I|archivedate=April 18, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/dont-look-down/id667736476?ign-mpt|title=''Don't Look Down'' by Skylar Grey|work={{noitalic|[[iTunes Store]]}}|publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|date=July 9, 2013|accessdate=July 9, 2013|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Hzoq2XVc|archivedate=July 9, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref>

Rihanna performed a short medley that comprised "Love the Way You Lie (Part II)", "[[What's My Name? (Rihanna song)|What's My Name?]]" and "[[Only Girl (In the World)]]" at the [[American Music Awards of 2010]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1652754/20101121/rihanna.jhtml|title=Rihanna Opens American Music Awards With Island Flavor|date=November 21, 2010|first=Mawuse|last=Ziegbe|work={{noitalic|MTV News}}|publisher=MTV Networks|accessdate=November 21, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFZVd5N|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> Another medley, consisting of "Love the Way You Lie (Part II)" and "I Need a Doctor", was performed at the 2011 Grammy Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2011/02/13/video-eminem-performs-at-grammys-with-rihanna-dr-dre-and-skylar-grey/|title=Eminem performs at Grammys with Rihanna, Dr. Dre, and  Skylar Grey|work=Rap-Up|publisher=Devin Lazerine|date=February 13, 2011|accessdate=June 21, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFe3jHP|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref>  While the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' considered the track an unnecessary sequel,<ref>{{cite news|last=Conner|first=Thomas|url=http://www.suntimes.com/entertainment/2896510,conner-rhianna-loud-review-111610.article|title='Loud' a well-deserved party for Rihanna|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|publisher=[[Sun-Times Media Group]]|date=November 12, 2010|accessdate=November 12, 2010|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DAw10jQo|archivedate=December 25, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref> the BBC reviewer James Skinner wrote, {{" '}}Love the Way You Lie (Part II)' even bests the original, Eminem's verse exuding the kind of volatile, simmering menace that got everyone so excited about him in the first place. But it is Rihanna's vocal<U+2014>at once commanding, soulful and vulnerable<U+2014>that anchors the song".<ref>{{cite web|last=Skinner|first=James|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/x5fd|title=Music&nbsp;<U+2013> Review of Rihanna&nbsp;<U+2013> Loud|work={{noitalic|BBC Online}}|publisher=BBC|date=November 15, 2010|accessdate=January 29, 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6DDFhwe7m|archivedate=December 27, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref>

