==Personnel==
The credits for "Love the Way You Lie" are adapted from the [[liner notes]] of ''Recovery''.<ref name="notes">{{Cite album-notes|year=2010|title=Recovery|albumlink=Recovery (Eminem album)|artist=[[Eminem]]|publisher=[[Interscope Records]]|publisherid=2739452|page=9|location=[[Santa Monica]]}}</ref>

* [[Eminem]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing engineer]], [[songwriting|writer]], [[Singing|vocalist]]
* [[Rihanna]]&nbsp;<U+2013> vocalist
* [[Skylar Grey]]&nbsp;<U+2013> writer
* [[Alex da Kid]]&nbsp;<U+2013> [[audio mastering|mastering engineer]],<ref name="rapup" /> mixing engineer, [[Record producer|producer]], writer
* Mike Strange&nbsp;<U+2013> mixing engineer, [[Sound recording and reproduction|recording engineer]]
* Marcos Tovar&nbsp;<U+2013> recording engineer
* Joe Strange&nbsp;<U+2013> [[Audio engineering|engineering assistant]]
* Spike Lindsey&nbsp;<U+2013> engineering assistant
* [[Makeba Riddick]]&nbsp;<U+2013> producer (vocals)
* J. Brow&nbsp;<U+2013> [[guitar]]ist

